''NOTE: Please refrain from making this entry redirect to blah. They are different words.''

== Interjection ==

1. A word used as an example where two different words are required.

''You can have an email address a different domain, so if bob@blah.com was taken you could get bob@bleh.com''

Blah is more usually used in preference to bleh, but there is a website poll at [http://freehost02.websamba.com/blahbleh/ www.blahbleh.tk] discussing which is more aesthetically and aurally pleasing. Note that "bleh" is almost never actually used in conversation or in writing.

2. SLANG A word used in conversation to reflect general indifference to a situation or object of conversation.

Eg. "I'm feeling a bit bleh." "Its all bleh."